The John Deere Pavilion landmark is part of the John Deere Commons in downtown Moline, Illinois. The pavilion opened in 1997 as part of an urban renewal project and serves as a visitor center for John Deere which has its headquarters in Moline. It also contains that largest store selling John Deere merchandise.
Opened in 1997, the pavilion has drawn over 200,000 visitors annually. It is one of the top attractions in the region and contributed directly to the development of other corporate visitor centers such as Coca-Cola and Caterpillar Inc..
